    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-01-15T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-01-15T08:00:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857/297</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-15T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 16, 5 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4882. The following note relative to the sinking of the English steamer <hi
                        rend="italic">Barbara</hi> has just been received: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="right">Foreign Office, <lb/> Berlin, January 14, 1917.</p>
                        <p>The undersigned has the honor to inform his excellency Mr. <persName
                                corresp="#p_GJW1">James W. Gerard</persName>, Ambassador of the
                            United States of America, in reply to the note of Mr. <persName
                                corresp="#p_GJC1">J. C. Grew</persName>, dated December 11 last
                            (Foreign Office No. 14836), on the sinking of the steamer <hi
                                rend="italic">Barbara</hi> as follows:</p>
                        <p>According to the investigations of the German naval authorities the
                            steamer <hi rend="italic">Barbara</hi> was stopped by a German submarine
                            with a shot of warning on October 20, 1916, a few miles south of the
                            Isle of Wight; the crew then immediately entered the boats. After the
                            commander had convinced himself that the crew had been taken on board of
                            the Spanish steamer <hi rend="italic">Victor Chavarri</hi> and was thus
                            in a place of safety he sank the vessel.</p>
                        <pb facs="0262" n="90" xml:id="pg_90"/>
                        <p>The undersigned requests that the above may be communicated to the
                            American Government and avails himself [etc.] <persName
                                corresp="#p_ZDA1">Zimmermann</persName>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
